<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFB7FFED6DC2FD3EFE11A9D4" pageId="19" pageNumber="1532" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFB7FFED6DC2FD3EFE11A9D4" blockId="19.[178,1085,675,726]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1532">
Etymology: The specific epithet 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFB7FFED6F3CFD39FD33A9BB" box="[588,678,676,697]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1532">graminis</emphasis>
(= grass) is a Latin noun. I refer to the straw-colored elytra.
</paragraph>
